  "rationale": "WoodWave lacks a logo-wall and feature-grid, so the brief's social proof and value props are mapped onto editorial vocabulary. The hero bookend is the only inverse, accent-bearing section, using the sanctioned display-title-over-media plus overlap. Gallery (collage) reuses the mosaic-with-overflow pattern with ghost-word + bleed + marginal-caption to answer no-text-on-photos. The three value_props render as one cards run of feature-items (staggered, asymmetric) rather than a boxed grid to respect no-cards-on-cream. Social proof adapts to an interlock float-wrap with the stat as headline and quote wrapping an inset image on a dark panel \u2014 the only place a bounded unit is legal. The conversion stack closes centered, per the centering exception. Each section is a distinct archetype (split, collage, cards, interlock, stack) for maximum structural contrast."
